<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 12 at 1:55PM ADT  by NWS San Juan</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm is affecting San Sebastian and nearby
municipalities, and another one from Yauco to Maricao through 200 PM
AST...
At 1253 PM AST, a cluster of thunderstorms was affecting the
northwest and southwest sections of Puerto Rico, with one storm near
San Sebastian, and another one around Yauco and Maricao.
HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, frequent cloud to ground lightning and
heavy rain.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects. Heavy rain may cause temporary
street flooding especially in poor drainage areas.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning. Motorists
should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.</instruction>
